# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  KONI — .gitignore
#  Keeps generated, fetched, and RESTRICTED data out of the public repo.
#  See README → "License & data provenance" and the NOTICE file.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.venv/
venv/
env/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# --- OS / editor cruft ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# --- Patch backups (created by apply_flame_patch.py / apply_stream_patch.py) ---
*.bak
*.bak.*

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  KONI data — everything under data/ is built locally by the ETL or fetched
#  at runtime, and includes TLG-derived and unlicensed material that MUST NOT
#  be redistributed. Ignore the whole directory; keep the folder via .gitkeep.
#
#  This covers, among others:
#    data/raw/             cached scraped sources (incl. TLG HTML) — restricted
#    data/intermediate/    parsed per-source JSON, repo map, discovery cache
#    data/texts/           downloaded Greek TEI (CC BY-SA) — fetched at runtime
#    data/canon.json       canon built partly from restricted sources
#    data/canon.csv
#    data/diogenes.sqlite  Diogenes export of the canon (TLG-derived)
#    data/diogenes_canon.csv
#    data/bpe_vocab.json   BPE cache — rebuildable via scripts/build_bpe.py
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
data/*
!data/.gitkeep

# --- Generated analysis outputs (Flame batch / reports) ---
text_comparisons_*.html
similarity_heatmap.html
similarity_summary.tsv
linguistic_variations.tsv
dist_mat.npz

# --- Logs / temp ---
*.log
*.tmp
temp_corpus.txt
